criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  diagnosis of a solid malignancy cancer, (i) non-metastatic disease or (ii) metastatic
             disease;

          -  between 3 and 7 months after start of treatment with adjuvant or 1st line chemotherapy
             or with adjuvant or 1st line immunotherapy;

          -  life expectancy of more than 3 months.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  age < 18;

          -  insufficient command of the Dutch language;

          -  severe psychopathology, other than mood or anxiety disorder (e.g. lifetime history of
             bipolar disorder, schizophrenia, MDD with psychotic features, schizoaffective
             disorders);

          -  severe cognitive impairments (e.g. dementia);

          -  patients with a (indication of) brain tumor or -metastases;

          -  a history of severe drug or alcohol abuse within past 6 months;

          -  not competent in the use of a mobile phone

          -  no informed consent.
